HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 672
By Powell
A RESOLUTION to recognize the inaugural Broadway Block Party
in Nashville.
WHEREAS, the Volunteer State has a rich tradition in women's athletics, with
Tennessee colleges and universities having won national championships in several women's
sports; and
WHEREAS, the popularity of volleyball is growing rapidly among both athletes and fans
in Tennessee and across the nation; and
WHEREAS, on August 31, 2025, the Nashville Sports Council and ESPN will sponsor
the inaugural Broadway Block Party women's college volleyball tournament at Bridgestone
Arena in Nashville, a city that has become prominent as a host of major sporting events; and
WHEREAS, the first women's collegiate volleyball tournament to be held in Bridgestone
Arena, the 2025 Broadway Block Party will feature some of the nation's elite volleyball athletes
playing in three SEC versus Big 10 contests, with all matches being nationally televised; and
WHEREAS, the first match pits five-time national champion Nebraska against defending
SEC champion Kentucky; and
WHEREAS, the second match will feature Purdue versus the Tennessee Lady Vols;
both teams have made four consecutive NCAA tournament appearances and both have
recently advanced to the regional semifinals; and
WHEREAS, in the final match of the tripleheader, Illinois, a veteran of twenty-eight
NCAA tournaments, will play the hometown favorite Vanderbilt Commodores, who will be
opening their historic inaugural season in Division I; and
